Synopses:
---------


Gosaipur Sorgorom:

	Feluda is called to Gosaipur by Jiban Mallik, the son of the local Zamindar Shyamlal Mallik to investigate a threat to his father's life. Everyone in the village knows that father and son are at loggerheads. Shyamlal is also an eccentric who eschews anything modern. Then, instead of Shyamlal, his son Jiban Mallik is killed and the wealth of the Mallik's looted. Oddly though, the dead body of Jiban Mallik vanishes, only to reappear again. What actually happened? Who is the criminal? Feluda works this out with a mixture of investigative skills and deception..

Joto Kando Kathmandute: 

	A gentleman called Mr. Batra comes to Feluda to say that someone is impersonating him. Another client, Anikendra Shome, is murdered, ostensibly by Batra's lookalike. The leads point towards Kathmandu and the three musketeers have to go there. In Kathmandu Feluda meets up with his old foe Maganlal Meghraj. What is Meghraj up to this time, apart from tormenting Jatayu? And what role does the famous doctor, Dibakar have to play in the whole affair? It is up to Feluda to uncover the truth about Meghraj once again...

Ekei Bole Shooting:

	The making of Feluda 30. Or more correctly snippets from the shootings. Did you know that Sabyasachi filmed a scene in Gosaipur Sorgorom with a broken foot and in bandages? that he also ran a 100 yards with that broken foot? or that one scene of a few seconds in Baksho Rahossyo was shot partly in Shimla and partly in Sikkim? Watch this episode to see these and other incidents...



Comments:
---------

The second of the two disc AVCHD uploads of Feluda 30. This set has three interesting little bits that I must share with you. 

First, &quot;Joto Kando Kathmandute&quot; is the only Feluda film that has been made in Hindi as well. It was called &quot;Kissa Kathmandu Ka&quot; with Shashi Kapoor playing Feluda. That is surprising, given that the English translation and compilation of the Feluda books is also a best seller. Perhaps it is because Sandip Ray does not sell the film rights of Satyajit Rays books, fearing what the Hindi Film makers would do with Feluda.

Second, Both Robi Ghosh &amp; Anupkumar played Jatayu in just two films each. Each disc in this collection has one film of Robi Ghosh and one of Anupkumar. Incidentally both died soon after they played their second role...

Third, Feluda went abroad for the first time in &quot;Joto Kando Kathmandute&quot;... Later of course he was to go to many cities that Satyajit loved. Interestingly, Feluda started out as the son of the Maternal Uncle of Topshe in his first story (Darjeeling Jomjomat) and Topshe was Topesh Ranjan Bose. Fromthe secod story onwards, Feluda became the first cousin on Topshe's father's side and that is what he consistently remained ever after... 

 This completes the AVCHD uploads of Feluda 30. We will also upload all six films in AVC/X264/MKV format, but the MKV uploads will not have the Menu(s) described below.



